ts `-Pcoordinates=` must accept `k/n` shards so CI can parallelize. The harness must handle adding a new library without code changes (purely metadata-driven discovery).\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:129:        issue_coordinates=\\\"org.example:lib:1.0.0\\\",\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:148:            \\\"--coordinates\\\", \\\"org.example:lib:1.0.0\\\",\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:971:        pipeline_argv = [\\\"--coordinates\\\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates]\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:979:                \\\"--coordinates\\\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates,\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:990:        pipeline_argv = [\\\"--coordinates\\\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates]\\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:998:                \\\"--coordinates\\\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates,\\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:74:                patch.object(make_pr_not_for_native_image, \\\"find_issue_for_coordinates\\\") as find_issue, \\\\\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:22:| Maven coordinate | `--coordinates group:artifact:version` | yes |\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:145:    TestLoop --> RunTest[run_test_command<br/>'./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=...']\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:218:./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar --metadataOutputDir=<output_dir>/agent\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:219:./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> -PmetadataConfigDirs=<output_dir>/agent\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:17:   `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:23:   (`./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v>\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:101:    Agent -- pass --> Test[gradlew test<br/>-Pcoordinates=&lt;g:a:v&gt;<br/>-PmetadataConfigDirs=agent_dir]\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:125:  `./gradlew generateMe