:                [{\\\"coordinates\\\": \\\"org.example:demo:1.0.0\\\", \\\"version\\\": \\\"25\\\", \\\"nativeImageMode\\\": \\\"future-defaults-all\\\"}],\\n./forge/tests/test_local_ci_verification.py:538:            [\\\"./gradlew\\\", \\\"testInfra\\\", \\\"-Pcoordinates=org.example:demo:1.0.0\\\", \\\"-Pparallelism=1\\\", \\\"--stacktrace\\\"],\\n./forge/tests/test_local_ci_verification.py:568:                    [{\\\"coordinates\\\": \\\"org.example:demo:1.0.0\\\"}],\\n./forge/tests/test_local_ci_verification.py:636:                return {\\\"include\\\": [{\\\"coordinates\\\": \\\"org.example:demo:1.0.0\\\"}]}\\n./forge/tests/test_common_git.py:27:    def test_find_issue_for_coordinates_uses_exact_coordinate_match(self) -> None:\\n./forge/tests/test_common_git.py:43:            issue_number = common_git.find_issue_for_coordinates(\\n./forge/tests/test_common_git.py:54:    def test_find_issue_for_coordinates_picks_oldest_duplicate_exact_match(self) -> None:\\n./forge/tests/test_common_git.py:68:            issue_number = common_git.find_issue_for_coordinates(\\n./tests/src/com.thoughtworks.paranamer/paranamer/2.8.1/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/com.thoughtworks.paranamer/paranamer/2.8.1/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = com.thoughtworks.paranamer:paranamer:2.8.1\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:57:   ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:61:   ./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:65:   ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:69:   ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:74:GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:79:To exercise many tests at once, you can target all coordinates or a slice of the test space via the N/M shard syntax.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:81:All coordinates:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:84:    ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:85:    ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:86:    ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:91:    ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:92:    ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:93:    ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:96:### Listing available coordinates\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:98:To print all testable GAV coordinates while honoring the same -Pcoordinates filter semantics used by the harness:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:101:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:102:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:103:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:104:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:105:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact -PstrictCoordinates=true\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:108:In GitHub Actions, this task also writes a space-separated list to the GITHUB_OUTPUT key \\\"coordinates\\\".\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:113:To print deps.dev dependency graphs for resolved GAV coordinates while honoring the same `-Pcoordinates` filter semantics used by the harness:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:116:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:117:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=group:artifact\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:118:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:119:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:126:Each stage of the testing can be run with `-Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`. Here are the examples:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:128:./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:129:./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:130:./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:131:./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:132:./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:133:./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:134:./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:135:./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:136:./gradlew listLibraryJars -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:137:./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:138:./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:140:./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:149:./gradlew jacocoTestReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:151:The root jacocoTestReport is a harness wrapper that invokes the per-project task across matching coordinates.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:174:./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:178:- `generateLibraryStats`: recomputes selected coordinates and updates matching exploded stats files under `stats/`.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:185:./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:194:- `coordinates`: group:artifact:version (single coordinate only)\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:199:   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7